urns%20Out%20To%20Be%20Baby%20Growing%20In%20Bowel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%2037-year-old%20woman%20in%20France%20got%20the%20shock%20of%20her%20life%20after%20she%20learned%20that%20she%20was%20unknowingly%2023%20weeks%20pregnant%20with%20a%20baby%20growing%20inside%20her%20bowel.%20According%20to%20a%20case%20study%20published%20in%20the%20New%20England%20Journal%20of%20Medicine%2C%20the%20woman%20sought%20medical%20treatment%20after%2010%20days%20of%20severe%20abdominal%20pain%20and%20worsening%20bloat.%20Medical%20experts%20conducted%20a%20scan%20and%20revealed%20that%20she%20was%20growing%20a%20%26quot%3Bnormally%20formed%26quot%3B%20fetus%20inside%20her%20abdominal%20cavity%2C%20which%20sits%20in%20between%20the%20stomach%20and%20the%20bowel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nejm.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1056%2FNEJMicm2120220%3Fquery%3Dfeatured_secondary%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20doctors%20explained%20that%20the%20woman%20was%20experiencing%20an%20abdominal%20ectopic%20pregnancy%20-%20when%20a%20fertilised%20egg%20implants%20outside%20of%20the%20uterus%20and%20instead%20in%20the%20abdominal%20cavity.%20This%20condition%20mostly%20results%20in%20the%20loss%20of%20the%20child%2C%20however%2C%20miraculously%2C%20doctors%20in%20France%20successfully%20delivered%20the%20baby%20at%2029%20weeks%2C%20and%20within%20three%20months%2C%20the%20mother%20and%20her%20newborn%20child%20were%20discharged%20from%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor's%20efforts%20were%20astounding%2C%20considering%20the%20potential%20danger%20to%20the%20mother%20as%20ectopic%20pregnancies%20can%20cause%20internal%20bleeding%2C%20tube%20rupture%20or%20shock.%20It%20can%20also%20result%20in%20fetus%20death.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2023%2F12%2F12%2Flifestyle%2Fwomans-stomach-cramps-turn-out-to-be-a-baby-in-her-bowels-i-thought-i-had-seen-it-all%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20chance%20of%20losing%20the%20baby%20in%20this%20case%20is%20as%20high%20as%2090%25.%20And%20those%20who%20do%20survive%20have%20a%20one%20in%20five%20chance%20of%20having%20birth%20defects%20or%20brain%20damage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fdoctors-in-china-remove-60-live-worms-from-womans-eyes-4648855%5C%22%3EDoctors%20In%20China%20Remove%2060%20Live%20Worms%20From%20Woman's%20Eyes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20woman%20received%20medical%20attention%20in%20France%2C%20where%20doctors%20ensured%20that%20they%20waited%20until%2029%20weeks%20gestation%20to%20give%20the%20baby%20the%20highest%20possible%20chance%20of%20survival.%20Then%20utilising%20their%20skills%2C%20the%20experts%20made%20an%20incision%20in%20the%20woman's%20abdomen%20before%20placing%20their%20parent's%20baby%20in%20neonatal%20intensive%20care%2C%20in%20an%20incredibly%20successful%20delivery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20doctors%20have%20found%20an%20embryo%20growing%20in%20an%20odd%20place.%20As%20per%20the%20Post%2C%20a%20doctor%20once%20took%20to%20social%20media%20to%20share%20a%20case%20report%20of%20a%20fetus%20growing%20in%20a%20woman's%20liver.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20I%20had%20seen%20it%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Michael%20Narvey%2C%20of%20the%20Children's%20Hospital%20Research%20Institute%20of%20Manitoba%2C%20said%20in%20the%20clip.%20%26quot%3BWe%20see%20these%20sometimes%20in%20the%20abdomen%20but%20never%20in%20the%20liver.%20This%20is%20a%20first%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702444380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fh0353598_newborn-baby-generic_625x300_13_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F37-year-old-french-womans-stomach-pain-turns-out-to-be-baby