the%20movement%2C%20while%20exploring%20her%20own%20Muslim%20identity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20364px)%2085vw%2C%20364px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102120%2FLand-of-My-Dreams-Poster.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22364%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102120%2FLand-of-My-Dreams-Poster.jpg%20899w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102120%2FLand-of-My-Dreams-Poster-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102120%2FLand-of-My-Dreams-Poster-767x1024.jpg%20767w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688943%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22486%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20poster%20of%20%E2%80%98Land%20of%20my%20Dreams%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKhan%E2%80%99s%20documentary%20has%20now%20been%20screened%20at%20film%20festivals%20in%20Japan%20and%20Austria%2C%20gaining%20international%20recognition.%20In%20August%2C%20it%20won%20the%20prize%20for%20the%20Best%20Long%20Documentary%20at%20the%2015th%20International%20Documentary%20and%20Short%20Film%20Festival%20of%20Kerala%2C%20putting%20it%20in%20the%20running%20for%20an%20Academy%20Award%20in%20the%20feature%20documentary%20category.%20While%20the%20protests%20took%20place%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20Khan%20said%20the%20issues%20of%20Islamophobia%20across%20the%20country%20prevail%2C%20and%20she%20hopes%20the%20film%20continues%20to%20gain%20momentum.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKhan%20began%20filming%20during%20the%20protests%20at%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%20on%20December%2013%2C%202019.%20Here%2C%20police%20had%20retaliated%20violently%20with%20tear%20gas%20and%20batons%2C%20injuring%20students.%20In%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Khan%20said%20she%20was%20only%20visiting%20Delhi%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20as%20a%20graduate%20of%20Jamia%2C%20she%20felt%20a%20deep%20connection%20to%20what%20was%20happening%20and%20knew%20it%20needed%20to%20be%20documented.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20fear%20entered%20my%20mind%20that%20everything%20is%20going%20to%20change%20and%20Jamia%20is%20going%20to%20become%20this%20place%20where%20people%20will%20be%20scared%20to%20send%20their%20kids%20to.%E2%80%9D%20Khan%20said.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20went%20there%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20students%20escaping%20from%20the%20boundary%20wall%20of%20my%20department%20and%20I%20remembered%20that%20we%20used%20to%20nap%20in%20that%20lawn%20so%20fearlessly%2C%20and%20we%20used%20to%20study%20there%20through%20the%20night.%20Never%20once%20did%20I%20imagine%20that%20the%20police%20were%20going%20to%20barge%20in.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20anti-CAA%20protests%20brought%20out%20thousands%20from%20across%20India%20on%20the%20streets.%20The%20protests%20were%20in%20response%20to%20the%20exclusion%20of%20Muslims%20from%20the%20amendment%20that%20gave%20persecuted%20minorities%20from%20neighbouring%20countries%20eligibility%20for%20Indian%20citizenship.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20101-day%20long%20Shaheen%20Bagh%20demonstration%20from%20December%202019%20until%20March%202020%20followed%20the%20protest%20at%20Jamia.%20It%20was%20a%20peaceful%20sit-in%20led%20by%20women%20that%20blocked%20a%20key%20stretch%20of%20the%20highway%20between%20Delhi%20and%20Noida.%20Khan%20attended%20almost%20every%20night%2C%20sitting%20alongside%20other%20protesters%20and%20documenting%20their%20voices.%20Through%20her%20documentary%2C%20Khan%20captures%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20women%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20movement%2C%20and%20the%20love%20and%20acceptance%20they%20fostered%20at%20Shaheen%20Bagh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20404px)%2085vw%2C%20404px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102054%2FNausheen-Khan_Directors-photograph.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22404%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102054%2FNausheen-Khan_Directors-photograph.jpg%20837w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102054%2FNausheen-Khan_Directors-photograph-209x300.jpg%20209w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102054%2FNausheen-Khan_Directors-photograph-714x1024.jpg%20714w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688942%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22579%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENausheen%20Khan.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20sustain%20a%20protest%20for%20that%20long%20and%20to%20risk%20your%20safety%20and%20to%20kind%20of%20balance%20that%20with%20your%20daily%20life%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20easy%20to%20do%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khan%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%20just%20felt%20so%20much%20gratitude%20for%20them%20that%20I%20just%20became%20almost%20addicted%20to%20that%20space%20because%20I%20haven%E2%80%99t%20experienced%20anything%20like%20that%20before.%20And%20when%20I%20stood%20there%20on%20that%20lock%20national%20highway%2C%20I%20used%20to%20feel%20like%2C%20%E2%80%98Wow%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20witnessing%20this%20revolution%20happening%20in%20front%20of%20my%20eyes.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlong%20with%20documenting%20the%20protests%20themselves%2C%20Khan%20provides%20a%20candid%20look%20into%20her%20own%20journey%20accepting%20and%20embracing%20her%20identity%2C%20despite%20the%20fear%20she%20felt%20because%20of%20it.%20This%20decision%20to%20integrate%20her%20own%20story%20as%20a%20Muslim%20woman%20was%20one%20Khan%20said%20she%20debated%20for%20a%20long%20time%20into%20her%20editing%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20said%20she%20hopes%20that%20her%20personal%20storytelling%20will%20encourage%20other%20women%20to%20share%20their%20stories%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20realised%20that%20my%20experiences%20growing%20up%20and%20my%20experiences%20during%20the%20protests%20have%20value%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khan%20said.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20for%20me%20to%20use%20my%20own%20voice%2C%20not%20just%20to%20tell%20the%20story%2C%20but%20also%20to%20inspire%20people%20to%20have%20trust%20in%20their%20own%20voice%20and%20in%20their%20own%20stories%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20Muslim%20women.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKhan%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20is%20one%20that%20encapsulates%20the%20inner%20conflicts%20that%20often%20come%20with%20religion%20and%20demonstrates%20her%20realizations%20and%20growth%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20protests.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20I%E2%80%99m%20going%20to%20feel%20less%20proud%20of%20myself%20because%20of%20my%20name%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20really%20problematic.%20And%20if%20I%E2%80%99m%20going%20to%20continuously%20be%20this%20person%20who%20is%20blending%20in%20and%20camouflaging%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20kind%20of%20hiding%20my%20Muslimness%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20doing%20a%20huge%20disservice%20to%20all%20of%20these%20people%20who%20are%20collecting%20during%20this%20protest%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20doing%20a%20disservice%20to%20myself%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khan%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKhan%20said%20the%20issue%20of%20Islamophobia%20is%20ongoing.%20Through%20her%20film%2C%20Khan%20continues%20to%20be%20their%20voice%20from%20the%20outside%20and%20said%20she%20hopes%20audiences%20can%20also%20see%20the%20relevance%20of%20the%20film%20despite%20the%20protests%20having%20ended.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CJust%20because%20nothing%20is%20actively%20happening%20right%20now%20and%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20being%20beaten%20on%20the%20streets%20openly%20every%20day%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20it%20has%20stopped%2C%E2%80%9D%20Khan%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%20feel%20like%20this%20viciousness%20is%20growing%20every%20day%20and%20people%20are%20sporadically%20being%20affected%20by%20it%E2%80%A6%20Islamophobia%20is%20affecting%20people%20every%20single%20day.%20And%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20talk%20about%20it%20and%20we%20continue%20to%20treat%20it%20as%20something%20that%20happened%20in%202019%20and%20is%20over%20now%2C%20then%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20going%20to%20help.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702444256000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13102132%2FLand-of-My-Dreams-Still2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fshaheen-bagh-documentary-nausheen-khan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20documentary%20recollecting%20the%202019%20protests%20against%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20Nausheen%20Khan%20courageously%20captures%20the%20voices%20of%20protesters%20and%20embraces%20her%20own%20identity%20as%20a%20Muslim%20woman.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fshaheen-bagh-documentary-nausheen-khan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nayanthara%20adds%20another%20feather%20to%20her%20cap%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702444247000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105951015%2Cimgsize-68538.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fvideos%2Fetimes%2Fbollywood%2Fnayanthara-becomes-one-of-the-most-powerful-women-in-business-actress-thanks-husband-vignesh-shivan%2Fvideoshow%2F105951015.cms%22%2