to%20five%20minutes%20before%20the%20stated%20ending%20time%20to%20start%20what%20Rogelberg%20terms%20an%20adequate%20%26quot%3Bclosing%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20time%2C%20whoever%20is%20leading%20the%20meeting%20should%20succinctly%20recap%20what%20was%20said%2C%20what%20the%20next%20action%20items%20are%20and%20who%20will%20be%20directly%20responsible%20for%20completing%20the%20upcoming%20tasks.%20They%20should%20set%20specific%20deadlines%20and%20outline%20what%20follow-up%20is%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20end%20of%20the%20allotted%20meeting%20time%20has%20arrived%20and%20there%20are%20still%20undiscussed%20agenda%20items%2C%20the%20person%20who%20called%20the%20meeting%20should%20state%20what%20those%20outstanding%20items%20are%20and%20when%20those%20things%20will%20be%20discussed%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20finally%2C%20Rogelberg%20said%20leaders%20need%20to%20get%20better%20about%20ending%20meetings%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeetings%20that%20go%20over%20run%20the%20risk%20of%20creating%20resentment%20among%20attendees%2C%20who%20often%20have%20to%20rush%20to%20their%20next%20meeting%20and%20may%20worry%20about%20being%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20feeling%20sticks%20with%20you%20and%20negatively%20effects%20productivity%20afterward.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20people%20ruminating%20over%20a%20bad%20meeting%20and%20then%20infecting%20other%20people%20with%20that%20negativity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20next%20time%20that%20meeting-goer%20asks%20to%20bring%20up%20one%20last%20thing%2C%20politely%20smile%2C%20decline%2C%20and%20suggest%20they%20follow%20up%20with%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702443360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-01%2Fk89fgov_o