inistership%20issue%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20focus%20now%20shifts%20to%20the%20future%20of%20leaders%20like%20Jyotiradtya%20Scindia.%20Despite%20the%20decrease%20in%20his%20supporters'%20strength%20in%20the%20BJP%20legislative%20party%2C%20there%20are%20questions%20about%20whether%20Scindia%20will%20contest%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20and%20his%20potential%20influence%20in%20Cabinet%20formation%20in%20MP.%20Although%20some%20of%20his%20loyalists%20lost%20in%20the%20recent%20election%2C%20the%20BJP's%20remarkable%20performance%20in%20the%20Gwalior-Chambal%20region%2C%20including%20Scindia's%20former%20stronghold%2C%20has%20boosted%20his%20confidence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ASHUTOSH%20SHUKLA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Joins%2080%25%20of%20the%20World%20to%20Pass%20UNGA%20Resolution%20on%20Immediate%20Ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13081822%2FGBLYZAeXAAAN1Oe.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Less%20than%20two%20months%20after%20abstaining%20on%20a%20similar%20resolution%2C%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20new%20resolution%20adopted%20by%20United%20Nations%20General%20Assembly%20by%20an%20even%20larger%20majority%20that%20called%20for%20an%20immediate%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FUN_News_Centre%2Fstatus%2F1734686801699491975%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3EWith%20153%20votes%20in%20favour%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nearly%2080%25%20of%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20member%20states%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution%20%E2%80%9CProtection%20of%20civilians%20and%20upholding%20legal%20and%20humanitarian%20obligations%E2%80%9D.%20It%20was%20passed%20during%20the%2010th%20Emergency%20special%20session%20on%20UN%20on%20%E2%80%98Special%20Session%20on%20Illegal%20Israeli%20actions%20in%20Occupied%20East%20Jerusalem%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Occupied%20Palestinian%20Territory%E2%80%99%20on%20Tuesday%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F4NAO4%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Voting%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22419%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20October%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-refuses-to-back-landslide-un-general-assembly-call-for-humanitarian-truce-in-gaza%5C%22%3EIndia%20was%20among%2045%20nations%20that%20had%20abstained%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20voting%20of%20the%20resolution%20that%20had%20called%20for%20an%20immediate%20cessation%20of%20violence%20in%20Gaza.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FUN_PGA%2Fstatus%2F1717995977758384336%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3EThe%20October%2026%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20received%20120%20votes%20in%20favour%20and%2014%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20latest%20resolution%2C%20the%20opposing%20votes%20shrunk%20to%2010%2C%20which%20included%20the%20US%2C%20Austria%2C%20Czechia%2C%20Liberia%20and%20Pacific%20allies.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20number%20of%20abstaining%20nations%20reduced%20from%2045%20to%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UNGA%20majority%20backing%20the%20resolution%2C%20introduced%20by%20the%20Arab%20Group%20and%20the%20Organization%20of%20Islamic%20Cooperation%2C%20was%20even%20higher%20than%20those%20condemning%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20terror%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20on%20southern%20Israel%20killed%20more%20than%201%2C200%20people%2C%20with%20240%20others%20taken%20as%20hostage.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20offensive%20by%20Israel%20in%20Gaza%20has%20killed%20more%20than%2015%2C000%20people%2C%20as%20per%20UN%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20vote%20on%20the%20draft%2C%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20main%20body%20also%20decided%20the%20fate%20of%20two%20amendments%20proposed%20by%20Austria%20and%20the%20United%20States.%20While%20they%20received%20more%20%E2%80%98yes%E2%80%99%20votes%20than%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99%2C%20they%20were%20not%20adopted%20as%20they%20failed%20to%20garner%20favour%20from%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20membership.%20India%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20both%20the%20amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Austrian%20amendment%20had%20sought%20to%20specify%20that%20hostages%20were%20only%20held%20by%20Hamas%2C%20while%20the%20US%20called%20for%20an%20unconditional%20condemnation%20of%20the%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20on%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20adopted%20resolution%20stated%20that%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccatastrophic%20humanitarian%20situation%E2%80%9D%20in%20Gaza%20and%20also%20expressed%20concern%20for%20the%20suffering%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20population.%20It%20also%20underlined%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CPalestinian%20and%20Israeli%20civilian%20population%20must%20be%20protected%20in%20adherence%20with%20international%20law%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20for%20an%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20resolution%20demanded%20an%20%E2%80%9Cunconditional%20release%20of%20all%20hostages%2C%20as%20well%20as%20ensuring%20humanitarian%20access%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20explanation%20of%20vote%2C%20India%20mentioned%20the%20October%207%20terrorist%20attack%2C%20but%20again%20did%20not%20refer%20explicitly%20to%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20has%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution%20just%20adopted%20by%20the%20General%20Assembly.%20The%20situation%20that%20this%20august%20body%20has%20been%20deliberating%20upon%20has%20many%20dimensions.%20There%20is%20the%20terrorist%20attack%20on%20Israel%20on%207%20October%20and%20the%20concern%20for%20the%20hostages%20taken%20at%20that%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20India%E2%80%99s%20permanent%20representative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20noted%20that%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Can%20enormous%20humanitarian%20crisis%20and%20large%20scale%20loss%20of%20civilian%20lives%2C%20especially%20of%20women%20and%20children%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20the%20issue%20of%20observing%20international%20humanitarian%20law%20in%20all%20circumstances.%20And%20there%20is%20the%20endeavour%20to%20find%20a%20peaceful%20and%20lasting%20two-state%20solution%20to%20the%20long-standing%20Palestine%20question%2C%E2%80%9D%20asserted%20the%20senior%20Indian%20diplomat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStating%20that%20the%20challenge%20was%20to%20strike%20the%20right%20balance%2C%20the%20Indian%20statement%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgravity%20and%20complexity%20of%20what%20the%20international%20community%20faces%20is%20underlined%20by%20the%20Secretary%20General%20invoking%20Article%2099%20of%20the%20Charter%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20we%20welcome%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20international%20community%20has%20been%20able%20to%20find%20a%20common%20ground%20to%20address%20the%20multiple%20challenges%20facing%20the%20region%20right%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20calling%20for%20adherence%20to%20humanitarian%20law%20and%20voting%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution%2C%20the%20Indian%20statement%20still%20did%20not%20specifically%20mention%20the%20need%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20or%20a%20humanitarian%20pause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-refuses-to-back-landslide-un-general-assembly-call-for-humanitarian-truce-in-gaza%5C%22%3EIndia%20had%20abstained%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20resolution%20did%20not%20have%20an%20explicit%20condemnation%20of%20the%20October%207%20terror%20attack.%20It%20had%20then%20been%20among%20the%20handful%20of%20countries%20in%20the%20Global%20South%20which%20had%20not%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20ceasefire%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22h