0while%20South%20said%20that%20some%20fighting%20is%20normal%20and%20healthy%20in%20relationships%2C%20not%20all%20fighting%20is%20created%20equal.%20She%20said%20%26quot%3Bthat%20it's%20fighting%20fair%2C%20fighting%20towards%20a%20goal%20and%20not%20being%20defensive%20or%20using%20criticism%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20ultimately%20helps%20couples%20problem-solve%20and%20move%20forward%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20not%20able%20to%20do%20this%2C%20however%2C%20you%20might%20have%20taken%20the%20rug-sweeping%20approach%20%E2%80%94%20only%20for%20problems%20to%20rear%20their%20head%20again%20years%2C%20or%20decades%2C%20later.%20You%20may%20find%20yourself%20in%20the%20position%20of%20deeply%20loving%20someone%20that%20you've%20been%20in%20a%20relationship%20with%2C%20but%20wondering%20if%20they%20are%20still%20the%20right%20person%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouth%20shared%20some%20of%20the%20subtle%20signs%20you%20might%20be%20in%20the%20wrong%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20You%20argue%20as%20often%20as%20you%20have%20fun%2C%20if%20not%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20South%20said%20it's%20very%20common%20to%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-common-fights-couples-have-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecurring%20fight%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20your%20relationship%2C%20the%20severity%20of%20the%20arguments%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20frequently%20is%20it%20coming%20up%20as%20a%20topic%3F%26quot%3B%20South%20said.%20%26quot%3BHow%20frequently%20is%20it%20the%20start%20of%20a%20larger%20fight%20or%20disagreement%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20recurring%20argument%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20the%20end%20of%20a%20relationship%2C%20South%20said%20it%20could%20be%20good%20to%20speak%20to%20a%20couple's%20therapist%20and%20get%20some%20help%20if%20you%20can't%20get%20past%20one%20specific%20argument.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20being%20said%2C%20it's%20also%20good%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20how%20often%20you're%20arguing%20overall%2C%20and%20if%20it's%20about%20a%20host%20of%20other%20topics%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20have%20some%20fights%2C%20but%20do%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20good%20times%20than%20bad%3F%26quot%3B%20South%20said.%20%26quot%3BIs%20the%20balance%20off%3F%20Are%20you%20the%20kind%20of%20couple%20that%20spends%2075%25%20of%20the%20time%20fighting%20and%2025%25%20having%20fun%3F%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20so%2C%20she%20said%20that%20doesn't%20bode%20well%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsigns-youre-in-a-healthy-relationship-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehappy%2C%20long-term%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20You%20hold%20back%20parts%20of%20yourself%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESouth%20said%20that%20not%20everyone%20is%20comfortable%20with%20opening%20up%2C%20and%20that's%20ok.%20Some%20people%20are%20just%20naturally%20more%20extroverted%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there's%20a%20difference%20between%20being%20naturally%20reserved%20and%20consciously%20holding%20back%20details%20about%20your%20life%2C%20whether%20it's%20your%20ambitions%20or%20parts%20of%20your%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20probably%20have%20a%20little%20voice%20inside%20our%20head%20saying%2C%20'I%20don't%20really%20want%20to%20share%20more%20with%20this%20person%2C'%26quot%3B%20South%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frelationships-that-last-share-these-qualities-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elasting%20partnership%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20built%20on%20trust%20and%20the%20feeling%20that%20your%20partner%20is%20here%20to%20help%20you%20reach%20your%20goals.%20If%20you're%20hesitant%20about%20being%20your%20full%20self%20around%20your%20partner%2C%20it%20could%20mean%20that%20you%20don't%20think%20they'd%20have%20your%20back%20if%20you%20were%20authentic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20You%20keep%20wanting%20to%20change%20your%20partner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20South%20said%20some%20people%20accept%20each%20other's%20differences%20early%20on%20or%20break%20up%2C%20there%20are%20also%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20who%20commit%20to%20a%20relationship%20and%20they%20feel%20like%20can%20get%20past%20whatever%20differences%20they%20have%20with%20this%20person.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20as%20the%20years%20pass%2C%20they're%20disappointed%20when%20they%20can't%20get%20past%20these%20differences%20%E2%80%94%20or%20that%20their%20partner%20can't%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20though%20some%20people%20do%20people%20change%20over%20time%2C%20most%20generally%20stay%20the%20same.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20you're%20in%20a%20long-term%20relationship%20and%20continually%20trying%20to%20tweak%20your%20partner%20into%20being%20the%20person%20you%20want%20them%20to%20be%2C%20it's%20a%20likely%20sign%20the%20relationship%20just%20isn't%20a%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20One%20or%20both%20of%20you%20changed%20and%20grew%20apart%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20one%20or%20both%20people%20can%20drastically%20change%2C%20according%20to%20South.%20One%20person%20might%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fdidnt-want-kids-relationship-changed-my-mind-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echange%20their%20mind%20on%20having%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20go%20through%20a%20mental%20health%20problem.%20Or%20they%20might%20just%20realize%20they%20want%20completely%20different%20things%20in%20life.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20wondering%20about%20why%20you%20feel%20confused%20about%20your%20relationship%2C%20South%20said%20a%20good%20question%20to%20ask%20is%20%26quot%3BHas%20the%20person%20changed%20in%20some%20way%2C%20or%20have%20you%20changed%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20you%20do%20next%20will%20vary%20based%20on%20what%