0World%20Teach%20N%20Treat%20Toy%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221668%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20brown%20pet%20rabbit%20is%20eating%20from%20a%20square%20white%2C%20green%2C%20and%20blue%20puzzle%20toy.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F601c2bae5f153c001979b325%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221251%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20enriching%20puzzle%20toy%20challenges%20rabbits%20to%20use%20their%20problem-solving%20skills.%3Cp%3EHagen%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EForaging%20puzzles%20engage%20a%20rabbit's%20brain%20through%20their%20stomach.%20To%20access%20food%20in%20hidden%20compartments%2C%20a%20bunny%20must%20put%20their%20genetically%20wired%20problem-solving%20skills%20to%20good%20use.%20It's%20not%20just%20a%20way%20for%20rabbits%20to%20chow%20down%3B%20the%20work%20they%20put%20in%20to%20find%20their%20goodies%20is%20plenty%20of%20fun%2C%20too%2C%20Berman%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20World's%20Teach%20N%20Treat%20Toy%20is%20made%20specifically%20for%20providing%20mental%20stimulation%20to%20small%20animals%20like%20rabbits.%20Small%20pieces%20of%20food%20fit%20within%20eight%20shallow%20cups%20arranged%20in%20a%20square%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%2010-by-10-inch%20puzzle%20board.%20To%20get%20to%20them%2C%20a%20bunny%20has%20to%20nudge%20or%20lift%20the%20covers%20that%20keep%20them%20hidden.%20There%20are%20three%20levels%20of%20difficulty%20to%20excite%20both%20beginning%20and%20advanced%20players.%20This%20puzzle%20is%20made%20from%20plastic%2C%20a%20material%20that%20rabbits%20can%20neither%20digest%20nor%20regurgitate%2C%20so%20it%20should%20only%20be%20used%20under%20strict%20supervision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%20in%20rabbit%20toys%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22rabbit%20enrichment%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F601c722590dd450018a7affe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20variety%20of%20the%20best%20toys%20for%20rabbits%20will%20keep%20your%20bunny%20happy%20and%20healthy.%3Cp%3EMolly%20Wald%2FBest%20Friends%20Animal%20Society%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20experts%20say%20the%20best%20rabbit%20toys%20are%20chew-safe%20and%20made%20of%20natural%20and%20untreated%20materials.%20Cox%20says%20that%20a%20good%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20choose%20a%20toy%20for%20your%20rabbit%20that%20you%20would%20feel%20comfortable%20chewing.%20For%20items%20like%20puzzle%20toys%20that%20aren't%20specifically%20made%20for%20chewing%2C%20stay%20away%20from%20extremely%20small%20pieces%20of%20hard%20plastic%20or%20wood%20that%20can%20be%20swallowed%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20always%20supervise%20your%20bunny%20while%20they%20are%20playing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20threat%20to%20a%20rabbit's%20health%20is%20the%20possibility%20that%20they%20may%20chew%20and%20swallow%20something%20they%20cannot%20digest.%20Because%20rabbits%20cannot%20vomit%2C%20if%20they%20swallow%20something%20indigestible%2C%20it%20can%20block%20their%20intestines%2C%20leading%20to%20severe%20pain%20and%20death%20unless%20surgically%20removed.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20rabbits%20should%20never%20be%20given%20toys%20made%20from%20soft%20plastic%2C%20polyester%2C%20or%20cloth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20we%20selected%20the%20best%20rabbit%20toys%3Cp%3EWe%20selected%20the%20best%20rabbit%20toys%20based%20on%20their%20pet-safe%20materials%20and%20expert%20advice%20about%20what%20makes%20a%20good%20toy.%20Activities%20like%20chewing%2C%20hiding%2C%20and%20climbing%20are%20important%20to%20a%20rabbit's%20health%20and%20well-being.%20The%20types%20of%20toys%20on%20our%20list%20tap%20into%20a%20bunny's%20natural%20instincts%20to%20chew%2C%20dig%2C%20forage%2C%20toss%2C%20hide%2C%20and%20jump%2C%20although%20not%20every%20rabbit%20enjoys%20engaging%20in%20all%20six%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERabbit%20toys%20FAQs%3Ch3%3EWhat%20toys%20do%20rabbits%20like%20best%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERabbits%20like%20toys%20that%20can%20keep%20them%20engaged%20and%20active%2C%20says%20Cox.%20The%20best%20rabbit%20toys%20keep%20a%20bunny%20mentally%20stimulated%20and%20provide%20fun%20opportunities%20for%20play.%20These%20toys%20may%20make%20noise%2C%20have%20texture%2C%20or%20feature%20bright%20colors.%20But%20it's%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20rabbits%20are%20relatively%20fragile%20animals%2C%20and%20even%20toys%20and%20experiences%20that%20seem%20harmless%20can%20cause%20severe%20health%20problems%20or%20even%20death.%20Just%20because%20a%20bunny%20is%20interested%20in%20chewing%20a%20corner%20of%20the%20carpet%20or%20hopping%20into%20the%20backyard%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20good%20for%20them.%20%26quot%3BThese%20guys%20are%20so%20domesticated%20that%20they%20can't%20tell%20what's%20safe%20and%20what's%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Berman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20best%20chew%20toys%20for%20rabbits%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERabbits%20are%20born%20chewers%20whose%20teeth%20continue%20to%20grow%20throughout%20their%20lives.%20To%20keep%20their%20teeth%20in%20check%2C%20it's%20essential%20they%20have%20the%20right%20outlets%20for%20chewing.%20Toys%20for%20chewing%20should%20be%20made%20of%20natural%20and%20untreated%20materials%20that%20won't%20harm%20a%20rabbit%20if%20ingested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bunny's%20front%20teeth%20and%20back%20teeth%20function%20differently.%20The%20front%20incisors%20make%20a%20snipping%20motion%20for%20chomping%20off%20pieces%20of%20grass%20and%20hay%2C%20while%20the%20back%20teeth%20grind%20from%20side%20to%20side.%20It's%20in%20those%20back%20teeth%20that%20Stern%20most%20often%20sees%20problems.%26quot%3BIf%20they%20don't%20chew%20on%20enough%20fibrous%20material%2C%20their%20teeth%20get%20elongated%20and%20it%20causes%20pain%20and%20can%20actually%20lead%20to%20them%20being%20unable%20to%20eat%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChew%20toys%20help%20wear%20down%20the%20front%20teeth%20but%20not%20the%20back%20teeth.%20And%20while%20rabbits%20do%20grind%20their%20teeth%20when%20content%2C%20similar%20to%20purring%20in%20a%20cat%2C%20keeping%20their%20back%20teeth%20healthy%20largely%20depends%20on%20providing%20them%20with%20a%20diet%20that%20contains%20tough%20hay%20and%20grasses%20like%20timothy%20and%20orchard.%20As%20they%20chew%20these%20fibrous%20materials%2C%20they%20gradually%20wear%20down%20growing%20back%20teeth%2C%20like%20a%20nail%20file%20removes%20excess%20fingernail%20growth.%20Help%20them%20keep%20their%20back%20teeth%20healthy%20by%20stuffing%20rolling%20balls%2C%20hanging%20toys%2C%20activity%20tables%2C%20and%20any%20other%20loosely%20woven%20toy%20with%20pieces%20of%20hay%20for%20bunnies%20to%20extract%20and%20snack%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20some%20homemade%20toys%20for%20rabbits%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20our%20experts%2C%20fun%2C%20enriching%20toys%20are%20easy%20to%20make%20from%20items%20you%20already%20have%20at%20home%2C%20like%20paper%20bags%20and%20boxes.%20Their%20suggestions%20include%20the%20following%20items%3A%20brown%20paper%20lunch%20bags%20stuffed%20with%20hay%20and%20greens%20and%20tied%20at%20the%20top%20for%20chewing%3B%20brown%20paper%20grocery%20bags%20for%20hiding%3B%20cardboard%20boxes%2C%20with%20tape%20or%20staples%20removed%2C%20for%20chewing%2C%20hiding%20in%2C%20and%20climbing%20on%3B%20metal-free%2C%20untreated%20wooden%20slotted%20clothespins%20for%20chewing%3B%20untreated%20straw%20or%20wicker%20baskets%20and%20placemats%20for%20digging%20and%20chewing%3B%20paper%20towel%20and%20toilet%20paper%20rolls%20stuffed%20with%20hay%20and%20greens%20for%20chewing%3B%20newspaper%20(black%20and%20white%20only%20to%20prevent%20digestive%20issues%2C%20no%20color%20inserts)%20for%20digging%20and%20chewing%3B%20mason%20jar%20cover%20rings%20for%20tossing%3B%20pine%20cones%20and%20fruit%20tree%20and%20willow%20branches%20for%20chewing%3B%20and%20egg%20cartons%20stuffed%20with%20hay%20or%20greens%20for%20chewing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20best%20indoor%20bunny%20habitat%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20rabbit%20toys%20are%20important%20to%20a%20rabbit's%20mental%20and%20physical%20health%2C%20but%20they%20are%20just%20one%20of%20a%20handful%20of%20essentials%20a%20bunny%20needs%20for%20an%20enriched%20life.%20To%20create%20an%20ideal%20bunny%20environment%2C%20our%20experts%20recommend%20bunny-proofing%20a%20well-lit%2C%20well-ventilated%20room%20or%20the%20whole%20home%20to%20create%20a%20rabbit%20den%20that%20the%20family%20will%20use%20regularly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAngie%20Green%2C%20founder%20of%C2%A0rabbit%20rescue%20organization%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspecialbunny.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Special%20Bunny%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recommends%20providing%20an%20enclosure%20with%20plenty%20of%20space%20for%20rabbits%20to%20run%20and%20stretch.%20Because%20rabbits%20are%20social%20animals%2C%20you%20should%20never%20isolate%20them%20in%20a%20basement%20or%20garage%2C%20where%20people%20rarely%20go.%20If%20there%20are%20other%20pets%20in%20the%20home%20that%20may%20antagonize%20the%20bunny%2C%20they%20should%20be%20kept%20out%20of%20the%20rabbit%20room%20at%20all%20times.%20But%20even%20if%20your%20bunny%20gets%20along%20with%20the%20cats%20and%20dogs%2C%20a%20space%20of%20their%20own%20can%20help%20them%20rest%20and%20recharge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20also%20want%20to%20provide%20your%20bunny%20with%20access%20to%20a%20long%20hallway%20or%20open%20space%20for%20running%2C%20jumping%2C%20and%20binkies%20(jumping%20twists%20a%20bunny%20does%20when%20happy).%20If%20your%20floors%20are%20bare%2C%20Berman%20recommends%20putting%20down%20nonslip%20flooring%20so%20your%20bunny%20can%20get%20traction%20as%20they%20play.%3C