20subsequently%20sought%20to%20ensure%20that%20her%20own%20four%20children%20were%20close.%20%26quot%3BJust%20know%20that%20you%20can%20find%20sisterhood%2C%20brotherhood%20outside%20of%20your%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BFamily%20isn't%20always%20blood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFavoritism%20and%20parental%20fighting%20can%20pull%20siblings%20apart%2C%20a%20psychologist%20warned%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Karen%20Gail%20Lewis%2C%20a%20therapist%20who's%20been%20practicing%20for%2051%20years%20and%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrkarengaillewis.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewritten%20books%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20sibling%20estrangement%2C%20concurs%20that%20parents%20are%20most%20often%20the%20root%20cause.%20But%20because%20dynamics%20are%20passed%20down%20through%20generations%2C%20she%20uses%20this%20conceit%20in%20her%20practice%20to%20explain%20rather%20than%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20most%20parents%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20do%20the%20very%20best%20they%20know%20how%20to%20do%20given%20their%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20favoritism%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bmost%20obvious%26quot%3B%20precipitating%20factor%2C%20Dr.%20Lewis%20said%2C%20some%20parents%20are%20consumed%20by%20in-fighting%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20kids%20to%20withdraw%2C%20take%20sides%2C%20or%20recreate%20the%20conflict%20within%20other%20relationships.%20When%20there%20is%20severe%20trauma%20at%20home%2C%20such%20as%20alcoholism%20or%20abuse%2C%20children%20%26quot%3Beither%20pull%20apart%20so%20they%20have%20no%20connection%20to%20each%20other%20or%20they%20pull%20together%20for%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20question%20Dr.%20Lewis%20asks%20patients%20is%20whether%20they%20were%20close%20to%20their%20siblings%20as%20young%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20namely%20from%20birth%20to%20the%20age%20of%20eight%20or%20nine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20ages%20are%20critical%20in%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20gets%20recreated%20many%20years%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20It's%20also%20easier%20to%20fix%20a%20conflict%20when%20there's%20some%20semblance%20of%20foundation.%20If%20not%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20to%20create%20something%20new%20that%20was%20never%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESiblings%20often%20reconnect%20later%20in%20life%20after%20a%20period%20of%20distance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20feeling%20like%20a%20relationship%20has%20become%20superficial%20to%20total%20cutoff%2C%20estrangement%20exists%20on%20a%20spectrum%2C%20Dr.%20Lewis%20explained.%20But%20there's%20often%20hope%20if%20the%20relationship%20isn't%20completely%20severed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20study%2C%20she%20said%20she's%20observed%20an%20%26quot%3Bhourglass%20pattern%2C%26quot%3B%20whereby%20kids%20are%20close%20growing%20up%2C%20then%20become%20distant%20into%20adulthood%20as%20they%20establish%20their%20own%20professional%20lives%20and%20families.%20But%20later%20in%20life%2C%20they%20often%20come%20back%20together%20as%20they%20leave%20the%20workplace%2C%20their%20children%20grow%20up%2C%20and%20their%20parents%20pass%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20her%20work%2C%20she%20said%2C%20occurs%20with%20patients%20who%20have%20experienced%20a%20crisis%2C%20like%20the%20death%20of%20a%20parent%2C%20which%20precipitates%20reconciliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20looking%20for%20some%20advice%20ahead%20of%20the%20holidays%2C%20Dr.%20Lewis%20advises%20not%20speaking%20about%20your%20sibling%20to%20or%20through%20a%20parent.%20Instead%2C%20she%20suggests%20meeting%20one-on-one%2C%20on%20neutral%20ground%20(like%20a%20coffee%20shop)%20for%20a%20catch-up%20before%20any%20family%20gatherings.%20Going%20directly%20to%20the%20family%20home%20can%20cause%20people%20to%20revert%20to%20%26quot%3Bold%20childhood%20patterns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20general%20piece%20of%20advice%2C%20if%20you%20want%20a%20relationship%20with%20your%20sibling%2C%20you%20have%20to%20keep%20the%20parents%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsiblings-once-close-grieving-estrangement-drifting-apart-as-adults-holiday-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702420043000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578d2b00ec98e92f74ebfbe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsiblings-once-close-grieving-estrangement-drifting-apart-as-adults-holiday-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22TikTokers%20are%20convinced%20that%20it%20starts%20with%20our%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20but%20an%20expert%20said%20reconciliation%20often%20occurs%20later%20in%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Geoff%20Weiss)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsiblings-once-close-grieving-estrangement-drifting-apart-as-adults-holiday-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20developer%20behind%20one%20of%20this%20year's%20most%20anticipated%20games%20just%20shut%20down%20after%20releasing%20its%20game%20on%20early%20access%20to%20disastrous%20reviews%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20gameplay%20in%20post-apocalyptic%20MMO%20The%20Day%20Before%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6578c00d50edbc52a86377d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22337%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Day%20Before%26quot%3B%20went%20from%20one%20of%20the%20most%20anticipated%20games%20of%20the%20year%20to%20receiving%20a%20flood%20of%20negative%20reviews.%20Now%2C%20the%20developers%20behind%20the%20game%20are%20closing%20up%20shop.%3Cp%3EMytona%20Fntastic%2FSteam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Day%20Befo