20centres%20in%20India%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fril-brookfield-infra-digital-realty-set-up-data-centre-joint-venture-123121201346_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fril-brookfield-infra-digital-realty-set-up-data-centre-joint-venture-123121201346_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fril-brookfield-infra-digital-realty-set-up-data-centre-joint-venture-123121201346_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rajya%20Sabha%20Passes%20Bill%20To%20Appoint%20Election%20Commissioners%2C%20Opposition%20Walks%20Out%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12231906%2FScreenshot-2023-12-12-at-11.18.33%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Bill%20to%20appoint%20the%20three%20members%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20was%20passed%20by%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20December%2012%2C%20amidst%20a%20walkout%20by%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20And%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20August%2010%2C%202023%20and%20moved%20for%20consideration%20and%20passage%20on%20Tuesday%20by%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20in%20the%20upper%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20government%20proposed%20some%20amendments%20to%20the%20Bill%2C%20which%20repeals%20the%20Election%20Commission%20(Conditions%20of%20Service%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20Transaction%20of%20Business)%20Act%2C%201991%20to%20provide%20for%20the%20appointment%20process%20and%20conditions%20of%20services%20for%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20two%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20biggest%20concession%20made%20by%20the%20government%20is%20to%20retain%20the%20status%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20the%20ECs%20on%20par%20with%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20following%20protests%20by%20opposition%20parties%20and%20former%20chief%20election%20commissioners.%20The%20Bill%20had%20earlier%20proposed%20to%20downgrade%20their%20status%20to%20that%20of%20the%20cabinet%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%2C%20however%2C%20is%20about%20the%20members%20of%20the%20selection%20committee.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fread-salient-sections-from-scs-judgment-on-appointments-to-election-commission%5C%22%3Eearlier%20this%20year%20ruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20approve%20the%20appointment%20of%20members%20to%20the%20ECI.%20In%20the%20new%20law%20that%20was%20proposed%20by%20the%20government%2C%20the%20CJI%20was%20substituted%20by%20a%20minister%20nominated%20by%20the%20PM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThough%20RJD%20MP%20Manoj%20Jha%20moved%20an%20amendment%20seeking%20to%20retain%20the%20CJI%2C%20it%20was%20defeated%20and%20the%20Bill%20passed%20by%20voice%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EComparisons%20of%20the%20two%20Bills%20indicate%20a%20clear%20climb%20down%20in%20several%20quarters.%20The%20selection%20committee%2C%20which%20was%20earlier%20proposed%20to%20be%20headed%20by%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%20and%20two%20secretary-level%20officers%2C%20will%20now%20be%20headed%20by%20the%20law%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EA%20new%20clause%20has%20been%20added%20to%20the%20Bill%20protecting%20the%20officers%20against%20civil%20or%20criminal%20proceedings%2C%20something%20that%20was%20omitted%20earlier.%20The%20courts%20are%20%E2%80%9Cprohibited%20from%20entertaining%20civil%20or%20criminal%20proceedings%20against%20a%20current%20or%20an%20ex-CEC%20or%20EC%20for%20acts%20done%2C%20or%20words%20spoken%20in%20the%20discharge%20of%20official%20duty%20or%20function%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20new%20clause%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBut%20it%20was%20protection%20from%20political%20interference%20that%20opposition%20MPs%20were%20more%20concerned%20about.%20While%20the%20CEC%20has%20the%20immunity%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20as%20far%20as%20removal%20from%20office%20is%20concerned%2C%20the%20two%20ECs%20can%20be%20removed%20at%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20CEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETMC%20MP%20Jawahar%20Sircar%20sought%20to%20extend%20this%20protection%20to%20the%20two%20ECs%20as%20well%20by%20amending%20Article%20324%20(5)%20of%20the%20constitution.%20Giving%20the%20example%20of%20ex-EC%20Ashok%20Lavasa%20%E2%80%93%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commissioner-ashok-lavasa-known-for-dissent-in-ec-may-leave-early-for-adb-job%5C%22%3Eresigned%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20various%20investigative%20agencies%20filed%20several%20cases%20against%20him%20%E2%80%93%20Sircar%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CElection%20Commissioners%20can%20be%20removed%20at%20will%20and%20their%20tenure%20remains%20unprotected.%20Look%20at%20the%20case%20of%20Lavasa.%20Institutions%20are%20being%20weakened%20and%20destroyed.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20look%20at%20the%20CAG%20%5BComptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%5D%20as%20well.%20The%20PM%E2%80%99s%20right-hand%20man%20%5BG.C.%20Murmu%5D%20is%20the%20CAG.%20Now%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20get%20any%20reports.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20opposition%20has%20been%20calling%20this%20an%20opaque%20legislation.%20A.D.%20Singh%2C%20RJD%20MP%20commenting%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cstate%20of%20democracy%E2%80%9D%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20Russian%20oligarch%20told%20me%20recently%20that%20I%20am%20more%20unsafe%20in%20India%20as%20compared%20to%20Russia.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20legislation%20should%20be%20brought%20in%20to%20cleanse%20the%20system%20but%20look%20at%20electoral%20bonds%20that%20is%20making%20the%20system%20opaque%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20CPM%20MP%20John%20Brittas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ECongress%20MP%20Amee%20Yagnik%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CDuring%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct%20the%20EC%20needs%20to%20be%20most%20vigilant%2C%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%20tries%20to%20influence%20the%20voter%2C%20at%20this%20time%20the%20EC%20is%20not%20governed%20by%20laws%20but%20by%20rules.%20There%20is%20a%20constitutional%20vacuum%20especially%20where%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20select%20committee%20is%20concerned.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Congress%20MP%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%20referred%20to%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20on%20the%20appointment%20of%20election%20commissioners%2C%C2%A0Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20responded%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20parliament%20is%20the%20supreme%20body%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20lawmaking.%20We%20cannot%20suffer%20interventions%20of%20any%20other%20organ%2C%20be%20it%20executive%20or%20judiciary.%20Reflections%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20are%20not%20binding%20on%20the%20parliament.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vice%20president%20has%20been%20vocal%20in%20the%20past%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fjagdeep-dhankar-supreme-court-njac-basic-structure%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98basic%20structure%E2%80%99%20doctrine%3C%2Fa%3E%20established%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20He%20said%20he%20does%20not%20agree%20with%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20interpretation%20that%20parts%20of%20the%20constitution%20are%20beyond%20the%20reach%20of%20the%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20commissioners%20bill%20was%20passed%20by%20the%20upper%20house%2C%20even%20as%20members%20of%20opposition%20parties%20staged%20a%20walkout%20today%20in%20protest%20against%20what%20they%20have%20described%20as%20executive%20overreach%20and%20a%20chipping%20away%20of%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20election%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20was%20an%20urgency%20in%20aligning%20the%20terms%20of%20service%20of%20the%20ECs%20with%20norms%20prescribed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%2013%20signatories%20had%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fprominent-figures-urge-mps-to-align-election-commissioners-appointment-bill-with-sc-norms%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20recent%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20members%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20urgency%20underlying%20this%20appeal%20arises%20from%20reports%20that%20one%20of%20the%20incumbents%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Commission%2C%20Shri%20Anup%20Chandra%20Pandey%20will%20retire%20in%20February%202024%20and%20if%20the%20Bill%20gets%20enacted%20in%20its%20existing%20form%2C%20the%20process%20of%20appointment%20of%20his%20successor%20will%20become%20completely%20non-transparent%2C%20making%20it%20possible%20for%20the%20NDA%20government%20to%20have%20a%20candidate%20exclusively%20of%20its%20choice%20appointed%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20dates%20on%20which%20elections%20to%20the%20parliament%20and%20several%20States%20are%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%2C%E2%80%9D%20read%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20present%20incumbents%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20are%20appointees%20of%20the%20political%20executive%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20their%20order%20of%20March%202%2C%202023%20%5BWP(Civil)%20No.104%2F2015%5D%20directed%20the%20government%20to%20consider%20introducing%20a%20more%20transparent%20system%20of%20their%20appointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702403594000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12231906%2FScreenshot-2023-12-12-at-11.18.33%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frajya-sabha-passes-bill-election-commissioners-opposition-appointment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20agreed%20to%20some%20concessions%20in%20the%20Bill%2C%20including%20retaining%20the%20status%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20the%20ECs%20on%20par%20with%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frajya-sabha-passes-bill-election-commissioners-opposition-appointment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Man%20accused%20of%20sending%20poison%20to%20people%20at%20risk%20of%20self-harm%20is%20charged%20with%2014%20murders%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702403340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F08%2F768x432%2Fskynews-kenneth-law_6261789.jpg%3F20230825031009%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fman-accused-of-sending-poison-to-people-at-risk-of-self-harm-is-charged-with-14-murders-13028893%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Canadian%20man%20accused%20of%20sending%20poison%20to%20hundreds%20of%20people%20at%20risk%20of%20self-harm%20has%20been%20charged%20with%2014%20counts%20of%20second-degree%20murder.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fman-accused-of-sending-poison-to-people-at-risk-of-self-harm-is-charged-with-14-murders-13028893%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fman-accused-of-sen